Chilean Stocks: La Polar Rises; Cap, Multiexport Foods Decline

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-06-23T15:10:55Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-23/chilean-stocks-la-polar-rises-cap-multiexport-foods-decline.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Chilean trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 10:42 a.m. New York time.  The Ipsa index fell 0.8 percent to 4,673.40. The  MSCI Chile (MXCL) 
index dropped 1.5 percent to 2,736.50.  Cap SA (CAP)  ,  Chile ’s largest steel producer and iron
miner, declined 2.4 percent to 21,050 pesos as commodity prices
fell. The Thomson Reuters/Jefferies CRB Index of 19 raw
materials dropped 3 percent, its largest intraday decline in six
weeks. Cap shares have lost 10 percent this month.  Empresas La Polar SA (LAPOLAR)   rose 14 percent to 616
pesos after shareholders approved a proposal to sell new stock
as the Chilean department-store seeks to avert a second
bankruptcy in 12 years. In a meeting in Santiago yesterday,
stockholders gave their consent for the sale of 250 million
shares to be priced at a subsequent meeting. Proceeds will help
make the company viable, Chairman Cesar Barros told reporters
after the meeting.  Shares have gained 31 percent in the past two trading
sessions after falling 67 percent in the prior two days. Volume
was almost double its daily three-month average.  Multiexport Foods SA (MULTIFOO)  , a Chilean salmon
farmer, declined 1.6 percent to 204 pesos as a rise in U.S.
jobless claims confirmed the  Federal Reserve ’s view that growth
in the world’s largest economy is slowing, eroding demand for
emerging-market exports. Multiexport sells its products to the
U.S. as well as  Japan ,  Central Europe  and parts of  Asia .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York 
